{"parentUuid":"dff109c9-c497-4530-9829-ee6ce191fec5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"8a0970a7-992a-482d-b1fb-9fa84d4f1b3d","agentId":"afcbc1ebf5764749c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WCZRZjcibp8KWQnJ4PBa8q","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"The error-envelope facade — every exception a handler raises terminates\n2\there, at one centralized boundary, as the single response shape:\n3\t`{\"error\": {\"code\", \"message\", \"requestId\"}}`.\n4\t\n5\tNever leaks a stack trace, exception type, SQL, or internal path to the\n6\tclient (ASVS 16.5.1/16.5.3) — the detail is logged server-side and the client\n7\tgets a generic, stable `code` plus the `requestId` that ties a user report\n8\tback to the server log line.\n9\t\"\"\"\n10\t\n11\tfrom fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException, Request, status\n12\tfrom fastapi.exceptions import RequestValidationError\n13\tfrom fastapi.responses import JSONResponse\n14\tfrom starlette.exceptions import HTTPException as StarletteHTTPException\n15\t\n16\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n17\t\n18\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n19\t\n20\t_STATUS_TO_CODE = {\n21\t    status.HTTP_400_BAD_REQUEST: \"bad_request\",\n22\t    status.HTTP_401_UNAUTHORIZED: \"unauthorized\",\n23\t    status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN: \"forbidden\",\n24\t    status.HTTP_404_NOT_FOUND: \"not_found\",\n25\t    status.HTTP_409_CONFLICT: \"conflict\",\n26\t    status.HTTP_413_REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE: \"payload_too_large\",\n27\t    status.HTTP_422_UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY: \"validation_failed\",\n28\t    status.HTTP_429_TOO_MANY_REQUESTS: \"rate_limited\",\n29\t}\n30\t\n31\t\n32\tdef _request_id(request: Request) -> str:\n33\t    \"\"\"Read the correlation id the logging middleware assigned to this request.\"\"\"\n34\t    return getattr(request.state, \"request_id\", \"unknown\")\n35\t\n36\t\n37\tdef _envelope(code: str, message: str, request_id: str) -> dict:\n38\t    \"\"\"Build the one response shape every error returns.\"\"\"\n39\t    return {\"error\": {\"code\": code, \"message\": message, \"requestId\": request_id}}\n40\t"}]},"uuid":"a75c5801-59e3-46b7-9b53-0bf4f3f7f78d","timestamp":"2026-07-09T04:00:57.768Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"dff109c9-c497-4530-9829-ee6ce191fec5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"a75c5801-59e3-46b7-9b53-0bf4f3f7f78d","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"afcbc1ebf5764749c","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcqpJwwKHx7e3od4vEbHu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":46,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4967,"cache_read_input_tokens":45707,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4967,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqpJvpbhPFNyrqXnQm4m","attributionAgent":"Explore","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"3ecbd9d7-e239-4ccb-8eca-e118d8ea0e30","timestamp":"2026-07-09T04:01:19.527Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"3ecbd9d7-e239-4ccb-8eca-e118d8ea0e30","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"afcbc1ebf5764749c","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcqpJwwKHx7e3od4vEbHu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've reviewed all the deleted/replaced areas. Here's my removed-behavior audit.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe change-set is overwhelmingly **additive** (a new metric-quotas feature). Almost every \"replaced\" line is a widening that carefully preserves the prior invariant, and I verified each re-establishment. Only one candidate represents a genuine reduction in guarantee.\n\n## Candidate (1)\n\n**`tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py` — AC20 absolute p95 budget assertion dropped, not re-established**\n\n- **Invariant the deleted code enforced:** AC20's absolute ingest-path budget (\"quota-active p95 < 50 ms\", per the docstring's own account of the prior form). The old assertion tied the quota path to a fixed millisecond ceiling.\n- **What the new code establishes instead:** only a *relative* bound — `quota_metrics[\"p95_ms\"] <= 1.5 * baseline_metrics[\"p95_ms\"]` (line ~437). The measurement *recording* is preserved (it still writes `events_baseline_metrics.json` / `events_quota_metrics.json`), but no assertion anywhere enforces an absolute ceiling.\n- **Failure scenario:** An unrelated ingest-path regression (e.g., a slow middleware added later, or a DB pool misconfig) that inflates p95 for *both* the no-quota baseline and the quota path equally — say baseline goes 85 ms → 900 ms and quota 87 ms → 950 ms. `950 <= 1.5 * 900` holds, so AC20 stays green while absolute ingest latency has regressed ~10x. The relative test cannot catch any regression that moves the baseline with it, and the sibling `test_events_ingest_sustained_500rps_k6_load` only asserts `sample_count > 0`, so no test in the suite guards an absolute ingest p95 anymore.\n- Caveat: this is a *documented, deliberate* human revision (the docstring argues the 50 ms absolute form is unachievable on the Docker-Desktop/Windows host). So it's a knowingly-accepted trade-off rather than an accidental drop — I flag it as PLAUSIBLE, not a clear defect.\n\n## Areas verified clean (invariant re-established)\n\n- **`src/api/errors.py`** — `_STATUS_TO_CODE` map is unchanged; the lookup became `getattr(exc, \"app_code\", None) or _STATUS_TO_CODE.get(...)`. Non-`AppError` exceptions map exactly as before (429→`rate_limited`); only `AppError`-carrying exceptions override. `AppError` extends FastAPI's `HTTPException`, so the `StarletteHTTPException` handler still catches it. No regression.\n- **`tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py` worker logic** — the 2-worker default is gone; both `_baseline_perf_workers()` and `_quota_perf_workers()` default to 5, and the new `test_ac20_quota_perf_fixture_matches_baseline_worker_budget` guard locks quota ≥ baseline. The pre-existing `test_events_ingest_sustained_500rps_k6_load` and `test_usage_read_...` tests are untouched.\n- **`scripts/ci/guard-source-markers.sh`** — the `MARKERS` regex is byte-identical to HEAD (line 49 unchanged); the only functional change is `EXCLUDE` adding `scripts/ci/guard-source-markers.sh`, pinned to that one filename (a marker in any other `scripts/ci/` file still blocks). No marker pattern lost.\n- **`scripts/ci/dast-review.sh`** — additive target-reachability probe; still `exit 0` always (advisory, never a gate). The `else`→`elif [ \"$REACHED\" != \"false\" ]` change only suppresses a misleading \"within budget\" line when the target wasn't reached; the advisory is emitted to stderr instead.\n- **`.claude/settings.json`** — the `deny` list keeps every prior approval-marker write-block and only *adds* denials (credential reads) and an `ask` tier; `Write`/`Edit` narrowing to `./**` is reinforced by the new `autoMode.hard_deny`. Deny still overrides allow for the `.pipeline/*-approved` markers.\n- **`.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml`** — the new `mutation` job is gated `if: false` and hard-wired `exit 0` (advisory); existing build/test/sast jobs unchanged.\n- **`src/db/session.py`, `conftest.py`, `middleware.py` (CORS +PUT), `api_key.py`/`api_keys_repo.py`/`seed_api_key.py` (scope column)** — all additive with defaults (`scope=\"ingest\"`) that keep existing callers behaving identically.\n\nNo other removed-behavior candidates found."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":46,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4967,"cache_read_input_tokens":45707,"output_tokens":2762,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4967},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":46,"output_tokens":2762,"cache_read_input_tokens":45707,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4967,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4967,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqpJvpbhPFNyrqXnQm4m","attributionAgent":"Explore","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"d7d8e052-b977-49e3-a8c5-49fd8bd11b13","timestamp":"2026-07-09T04:01:40.713Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
